<br>
- As stated above, the Post-50 firepets autocast on themselves <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> immediately</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> after summoning, and recast regularly. <br>
<br>
- Mobs recast their buffs regularly, and even maintain short-duration buffs such as &quot;Cadeau of Flame&quot; (as opposed to long duration buffs like &quot;Spirit of the Wolf&quot;). <br>
<br>
- The Epic pet's DS, the Pre-50 fire pet's DS, and the Decoy Pet's DS (DDD and Pre-50 Fire use the same DS spell) are also effectively <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> perminent</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> buffs, and these will generally never be recast unless dispelled. <br>
<br>
If you want to reduce resources based on spellcasting NPC's, add a 200% or perminent duration modifier to non-pet NPC cast spells, or a 'minimum' duration of 20 minutes. One can 'assume' these mobs will always have this buff cast on them (on or recast within seconds), so there is absolutely no reason to make them recast the spells as often as they do.<br>
<br>
There are far more NPC's in the game than player-cast Epic/Fire pets. Reductions in processing time there provide better savings than limiting player pets this way. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
Conjurer of the 57th Season<BR>
